{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Conduct a review of working conditions in the security industry",
        "additional_details": "Frontline SIA security officers face frequent assaults, repeat offenders, and high-risk confrontations with little protection or legal backing. We think current training, equipment, staffing, and pay do not reflect these dangers. Without reform, officers will continue to be injured and threatened. The Government must review and make recommendations to improve safety, training, protective gear, and justice for assaults.",
        "background": "Review the security industry, including safety, training, equipment, and justice. Frontline SIA security officers face violence daily. We need stronger training, protective equipment, staffing rules and justice for assaults to keep them safe and supported.",
